txt.en: 'We may not be as grand as all the high folk in Michel Delving and Tuckborough, but we deserve the same respect.'
'I like living in my waggon. Who wants to live in some stupid hole in the ground anyway?'
'Folks are always coming through here. To them, we're just another stop on the road.'
'I don't mind living here, but I hope my children can move to Hobbiton one day or maybe Scary.'
